    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>Sept 29 1862</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Being unable to<lb/> attend to the packing of your<lb/> Books I find
                the person so doing has sent you all <sic>He</sic><lb/> found I think you will
                find<lb/> some Books of <persName>Isaac<lb/> Wise</persName> and one <sic>sett</sic>
                of German<lb/>
                <sic>Preyers</sic> not of your publication<lb/> please return by Express any books
                not belonging to you so <add>?</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your old friend <persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName></p>
            <p>I feel hurt your not sending me<lb/> the Occident as well as others<lb/> do &amp; I
                am willing to pay<lb/> for it I am as ever at your service</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">T. O.</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="The following is written in pencil at the bottom center of the page.">E</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>The <sic>Pourtigese</sic> Synagogue was<lb/> well attended during
                        <date>Roush<add>?</add> a<lb/> Shona</date>. <persName>Gutheim</persName>
                lectured<lb/> the first night &amp; such was his<lb/> eloquence that scarcely a Dry
                eye<lb/> among either sex. I attended the<lb/>
                <add>?</add> Synagogue the first day<lb/> it was not crowded but crammed<lb/> I
                never saw it so full by both sexes<lb/>
                <persName>Dr. Illoway</persName> Lectured both days<lb/> &amp; also <add>שבת</add>
                Shuvar (<date>repentance<lb/> day</date>) the <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> day
                    Roush a Shona</date><lb/> I attended the Polish Shool<lb/> They have a finely
                fitted up place<lb/> over the <placeName>Carrolton Rroad</placeName> Depot<lb/>
                Their Hazan has a magnificent<lb/> Voice but he did not read<lb/> the <date>2<hi
                        rend="sup">nd</hi> day</date>. Musaph was read in<lb/> a solemn &amp;
                beautiful style<lb/> by the Sandac. I was the<lb/>
                <sic>receipiant</sic> of many honors<lb/> &amp; kind attentions on the</p>
            <p
                rend="Vertical blue lines under writing on entire page. The following is written at the bottom of the page;"
                    ><date>9-29-1862</date> E</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>occasion &amp; was seated next to<lb/> their President <persName>L Kaiser
                    Esq</persName><lb/> Their Cemetery is nearly opposite that<lb/> of the
                    <sic>Pourtugese</sic> &amp; is beautifully<lb/> laid out while speaking of<lb/>
                Burial Grounds I must mention<lb/> the Rampart Congregation have lately<lb/> erected
                a massive &amp; beautiful brick<lb/> Wall all round their old cemetery<lb/> on
                    <placeName>Jackson St </placeName>&amp; the District. <sic>Haveing</sic><lb/>
                purchased &amp; laid out on family Lots<lb/> a very large piece of Ground at the<lb/>
                <placeName>junction of Gentilly<add>?</add> Road &amp; the<lb/> Ponchalian R
                    Road</placeName>. The style<lb/> of everything connected with it is on<lb/> the
                modern style &amp; a credit to the<lb/> Congregation <persName>Mr
                    Friedlander</persName> is still<lb/> their presiding officer &amp; does all<lb/>
                in his power to Benefit the<lb/> Congregation notwithstanding<lb/> nor <add>?</add>
                existing our Congregations<lb/> &amp; Benevolent Societies continue to flourish—</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">I H</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
